  "title": "Drafter",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job and responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<p>1. Prepare detailed drawings, plans, and layouts based on specifications, sketches, or instructions provided by engineers or designers.</p>\n<p>2. Ensure adherence to drafting standards, guidelines, and industry best practices while creating technical drawings.</p>\n<p>3. Utilize computer-aided design (CAD) software to create accurate and precise drawings, incorporating necessary dimensions, annotations, and symbols.</p>\n<p>4. Create and maintain comprehensive technical documentation, including drawings, schedules, and material list, for construction or manufacturing purposes.</p>\n<p>5. Make necessary revisions or modifications to drawings as directed by project managers or design professionals to accommodate changes or resolve issues.</p>\n<p>6. Collaborate with engineers, project managers and other stakeholders to understand design requirements, address queries, and coordinate drafting activities.</p>\n<p>7. Perform quality checks on drawings to ensure accuracy, completeness and compliance with design standards and project specifications.</p>\n<p>8. Organize and maintain electronic and physical files of drawings and related documentation, ensuring easy retrieval and version control.</p>\n<p>9. Any other ad hoc task from superior or management.</p>",
